SIMPLE: discussive
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: discussive
<hw>dis*cuss"ive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>discussif</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Able or
tending to discuss or disperse tumors or coagulated matter;
discutient.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Doubt-dispelling; decisive.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A kind of peremptory and <qex>discussive</qex> voice.</q>
<rj><qau>Hopkins.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Discussive</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Discussive
<hw>Dis*cuss"ive</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A medicine
that discusses or disperses morbid humors; a discutient.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Discutient</ent>⟦br⟧
